page.text: 2. Verify that there is sufficient room to add the future multi‐purpose room
and still meet the minimum County setback requirements.

text.b: RESPONSE: A future gymnasium is not part of this project and in included
for information only. There is sufficient space to build a 6,000 SF
gymnasium, similar to the one located at Live Oak Elementary School.
Attached is a preliminary conceptual floor plan outlining the possible
extent. The floor plan shown is a sample floor plan; an actual layout will
be designed based on the user’s needs, regulatory requirements and
available funding, if it occurs. With this layout the side setback of 21’
would meet the County’s current setback requirements per our initial
pre‐application meeting with the County in 2013. Currently there are no
plans to build a gymnasium as it is unfunded.
